The Department of Health is expected to publish the new COVID-19 regulations by midnight tonight. The current temporary regulations, following the suspension of the state of disaster, lapse at 12pm tonight. The department earlier gave an assurance that an announcement on new measures would be made in due course. Possible extension of government’s COVID-19 regulations as they expire: Prof. Mosa Moshabela  Department spokesperson Foster Mohale says: “The department of health is currently finalising an announcement on how the country will move forward in managing the current spread of COVID-19 and future medical conditions. We are currently inundated with media and public enquirers and we would like to assure the public that everything is under control. We are mindful that the current measures put in place are lapsing in the next few hours.”